Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportPipeline(25.10)                                    reportPipeline(25.10)

Name
       reportPipeline  - The command can be used for analysis before the flops
       exist in the netlist; or it can be used post flop insertion  to  either
       report  expected  average  wire-length between stages of a pipeline net
       group, or to report the achieved average distance  between  the  placed
       stages of the pipeline

Syntax
       reportPipeline

       [-help]

       [-netGroup <netGroupNames>]

       [{-spacing <value > | -timingBased  | -psPMBased } -file <fileName>]

       The  command  can  be  used  for analysis before the flops exist in the
       netlist; or it can be used post flop insertion  to  either  report  ex-
       pected  average  wire-length between stages of a pipeline net group, or
       to report the achieved average distance between the  placed  stages  of
       the pipeline. When used for analysis, the command reports expected num-
       ber of PFF stages for each net group based on the user-specified value.
       Optionally the command generates bus-guides for reported route-path.

Parameters
       -file <fileName>
              Specified  the  output  for additional information from the com-
              mand. The output includes expected placement location of PFF  at
              each stage in analysis flow.

       -netGroup <netGroupNames>
              Restricts  the report to the net group name specified. If no net
              group name is specified, all pipeline net groups are reported.

       -spacing<value>| -timingBased | -psPMBased
              Given the target approximate wire-length spacing between stages,
              -spacing suggests the number of flop stages to insert.

              -timingBased is used to automatically  estimate  the  number  of
              pipeline FFs needed, based on timing delay on routing layers and
              the  clock cycle requirement. It is mutually exclusive to option
              -spacing because the spacing can be decided automatically.

              -psPMBased is used to automatically find maximum  spacing  using
              pspm model.

Example
              * The  following  command  reports expected number of PFF stages
                for net group "netGroup1" if the distance between  each  stage
                is around 300 microns:

                reportPipeline -netGroup netGroup1 -spacing 300

              * The  following  command  reports  the  expected  number of PFF
                stages for net group netGroup1 if the  distance  between  each
                stage  is  around  300  microns. Additional information of ex-
                pected placement location of each stage  are  written  in  the
                file PFF.rpt:

                reportPipeline -netGroup netGroup1 -spacing 300 -file PFF.rpt

Related Information
              * createPipelineNetGroup

              * deletePipelineNetGroup

